PLEASE READ COMPLETE INSTRUCTIONS PRIOR TO USE. Remove SUBLOCADE from the refrigerator 15 minutes prior to administration. The product requires at least 15 minutes to reach room temperature, Attach the needle at the time of administration, Use only the needle provided. Store at 20-8°C (35.6-46.4°F). Once outside the refrigerator, this product may be stored in its original packaging at room temperature, 15°-30°C (590-86°F), for up to 7 days prior to administration. Discard SUBLOCADE if left at room temperature for longer than 7 days. Call for emergency medical help, Evaluate. and Support NARCANnaloxane HC) NASAL SPRAY 4 mg HAND SUPPORTS Gently insert the tip of the nozzle into either nostril. • Tilt the person's head back and provide support under the neck with your hand. Gently insert the tip of the nozzle into one nostril, until your fingers on either side of the nozzle are against the bottom of the person's nose. KNEE STOPS BOY FROM ROLLING ONTO STOMACH OPEN HERE FOR QUICK START GUIDE Opioid Overdose Response Instructions Use NARCAN Nasal Spray for known or suspected opioid overdose in adults and children. Peel back the tab with the circle to open the NARCAN® Nasal Spray NOZU Important: For use in the nose only. Do not remove or test the NARCAN® Nasal Spray until ready to use ASK person if he or she is okay and shout name. Check for signs of opioid overdose: Will not wake up or respond to your voice or touch • Breathing is very slow, irregular, or has stopped • Center part of their eye is very small, sometimes called "pinpoint pupils" PLUNGER Get emergency medical help right away. Move the person on their side recovery position) after ging NARCAN Nase Spray Watch the person closely. If the person does not respond by waking up to walce or touch.gr breathing normally another dose may be dven NARCAN Nasal Spray may be dosed every 2 to 3 minutes. If Svalable. Repeat Step 2 using a new NARCAN Nasal Spray to give another dose in the other nostril. If addition NARCAN Nasal Sprays are available, repeat step 2 every 2 to 3 minutes unt the person Nesponds or emergency medical helps received. This box contains two (2) 4-mg doses of naloxone HCI in 0.1 mL of nasal spray. Two Pack Hold the NARCAN®Nasal Spray with your thumb on the bottom of the plunger and your first and middle fingers on either side of the nozzle. Press the plunger firmly to give the dose of NARCAN Nasal Spray. • Remove the NAR CAN Nasal Spray from the nostril after giving the dose. Lay the person on their back to receive a dose of NARCAN Nasal Spray. CHECK PRODUCT EXPIRATION DATE BEFORE USE. EXP MMMYYYY LOT XXXXXX #NARCAN NASAL SPRAY Inabxone 10 This box contains two (2) 4-mg doses of naloxone HCl in 0.1 mL of nasal spray. 0.1 mL intranasal spray (2 units per box) NALOXONE HYDROCHLORIDE 4 MG TWO (2) SINGLE DOSES. FOR INTRANASAL USE AS AN OPIOID ANTAGONIST. PROTECT FROM LIGHT. STORE AT ROOM TEMPERATURE BETWEEN 59°F TO 77°F (15°C TO 25°C). EXCURSIONS PERMITTED UP TO 104°F (40°C). DO NOT FREEZE. See front panel and blister pack for quick start guide. Each 0.1 mL of NARCAN NASAL SPRAY contains 4 mg naloxone hydrochloride in purified water solution containing benzalkonium chloride, disodium ethylenediamine tetraacetate and sodium chloride buffered with sodium hydroxide/ hydrochloric acid to an approximate pH of 4.5. DO NOT TEST DEVICES OR OPEN BOX BEFORE USE. CHECK PRODUCT EXPIRATION DATE BEFORE USE. Measure the dose of medicine from the widest part of the plunger. Do not measure from the narrow tip. Refer to figure and Medication Guide. 1. Insert syringe adapter (bottle plug) into neck of the bottle, ribbed end first. ! 2. Insert syringe tip into hole on the top of the syringe adapter (bottle plug) until secure. I 3. Turn the bottle upside down. Pull back the plunger to the line that matches the dose prescribed by your healthcare provider. ! 4. Turn bottle right side up. Remove syringe by twisting. I 5. Take your medicine by slowly pushing the plunger until the oral syringe is empty. 6. Leaving the syringe adapter (bottle plug) in the bottle, recap the bottle tightly with the supplied cap. 4mg = 0.2mL 2mg = 0.1mL Measure the dose from the widest portion of the plunger.
